episodes.overview: Abby turns Sesame Street into a magical ocean so Dorothy can swim anywhere she likes but when she disappears, Elmo and Abby follow clues to find her. Also featuring Cookie Monster's Smart Cookies, and Elmo the Musical. Brought to you by the letter O and the nubmer 6.

episodes.name: Don't Get Pushy
episodes.overview: Telly is upset when Rosita pushes Baby Bear by accident because she is too excited; but with the help of her friends on Sesame Street, she learns how to control herself. Also featuring Cookie Monster's Les Moussarables, and Elmo the Musical. Brought to you by the letter E and the number 11.

episodes.name: School for Chickens
episodes.overview: Elmo helps Professor Buck Awe, played by Saturday Night Live's Taran Killam, teach a class of chickens using strategies he learned in preschool. Also featuring Murray has a little lamb, and Elmo's World. Brought to you by the letter S and the number 14.

episodes.name: Halloween
episodes.overview: In this special Halloween episode, the letter of the day is 'H' (for 'Halloween') and Elmo learns that a good imagination is the most important part of pretending.

46.name: Season 46
46.overview: Season 46 teaches smarter, stronger, and kinder lessons with fun and familiar themes like bedtime, boo-boos, and animals.

episodes.name: The Kindness Kid
episodes.overview: The Kindness Kid (Zachary Levi) visits Sesame Street to spread kindness and Grover wants to be a Kindness Kid too, but every time he tries to do something kind, he fails. Chris helps Grover realize that just trying to help someone is actually being kind.

episodes.name: Be Kind to Your Worm
episodes.overview: Oscar participates in the Be Kind to Your Worm day activities, because he knows it’ll make his best friend, Slimey, happy.

episodes.name: Abby Helps Clear Things Up
episodes.overview: Abby helps Prince Charming calm down at the eye doctor's office.

episodes.name: Super Sitters
episodes.overview: Grover and Cookie Monster help Chris baby-sit and learn how to take care of a baby.

episodes.name: Having a Ball
episodes.overview: When Saul the Ball is disappointed that he can’t play ball with Elmo and Rosita inside the house, Elmo and Rosita help him use his imagination to play other games.

episodes.name: Elmo's Sweet Ride
episodes.overview: Elmo shares his scooter with Zoe and learns how to be patient and wait for his turn, while she practices and learns how to ride.

episodes.name: Dress Up
episodes.overview: Abby and Elmo play dress up and pretend to be lots of different people, like bike repair assistants, to help Nina fix Rosita’s bike.

episodes.name: Snuffy's Dance (repeat)
episodes.overview: Zoe choreographs a ballet and the dancers must work together to figure out how to make Snuffy fly.

episodes.name: Norbert's Birthday
episodes.overview: Rosita, Zoe, and Grover give Norbert the Robot a surprise birthday party to show how much they care about him.

episodes.name: Elmo Comes Clean
episodes.overview: Elmo keeps hiding from Nina because he wants more time to play before his bath, but Ernie helps him realize that he can play in the bathtub, too.

episodes.name: Baby Bear Learns About Bees (repeat)
episodes.overview: Baby Bear is scared of bees until Abby shows him and Chris just how amazing the insects really are.

episodes.name: Big Bird's Song
episodes.overview: Abby and Elmo help Big Bird calm down, so he won’t be nervous singing on the show, “The Squawk.”

episodes.name: Get Ready for Today
episodes.overview: Elmo and Abby help Crystal the Ball come up with a morning routine, so she can be ready to go out and play.

episodes.name: Painting with Cookie Monster
episodes.overview: Cookie Monster learns how to control himself from eating his own paintings.

episodes.name: Meet Julia
episodes.overview: Elmo and Abby play with Julia, and Alan helps Big Bird understand more about Julia's autism.

episodes.name: Make Your Garden Grow
episodes.overview: Elmo has made sure his apple tree has good soil, water and sunshine, but he still needs to learn how to be patient and wait for it to grow.

episodes.name: Bike Show with a Beat
episodes.overview: Nina and her friends make musical instruments out of bike parts and play music to attract customers to her new bike shop.

episodes.name: Counting Hats (repeat)
episodes.overview: Elmo and Zoe compete to see who can wear the most hats.

episodes.name: House of Worm
episodes.overview: Abby helps Turner the Worm build a place that feels like home.

episodes.name: Wild Animals Shop for Lunch (repeat)
episodes.overview: Snuffy helps out at Hooper’s Store when zoo animals come for brunch, but has to find a way to remember everyone’s order. Guest star: Audra McDonald.

episodes.name: Sheep in a Jet Pack
episodes.overview: When Ovejita flies up high after putting on a jetpack, Abby and Nina must figure out how to get her back down.

episodes.name: Rocking Rollie
episodes.overview: Rosita and Zoe build a baby-rocking machine.

episodes.name: Elmo and Rosita's Rainbow Search (repeat)
episodes.overview: Elmo sees a rainbow, but it disappears before Rosita can see it. Rosita, who has never seen a rainbow, becomes determined to see one. Guest: OK Go.

episodes.name: Father's Day
episodes.overview: It’s Father’s Day, and Rosita’s friends help her make a video message, so she can tell her dad how much she loves him.

episodes.name: The Recycling Fairy
episodes.overview: Redusa the Recycling Fairy visits Sesame Street and helps everyone recycle their old trash into something new to help keep the earth clean and beautiful.

episodes.name: The Camouflage Game
episodes.overview: Elmo, Rosita and Chris try to find six camouflaged things on Sesame Street so they can join the Camouflage Club. Guest: Kyra Sedgwick.

episodes.name: Twinkle Twinkle Little Star
episodes.overview: Elmo doesn’t give up and keeps practicing until he can play the song “Twinkle Twinkle Little Star” on his piano. Guest: 5th Harmony.

episodes.name: Bert and Ernie Make a Movie (repeat)
episodes.overview: Ernie and Elmo help Bert tap into his imagination as he acts out different scenes for a movie.

episodes.name: Big Bird’s Big Move
episodes.overview: Freddy Flapman, real estate agent to birds, tries to convince Big Bird to migrate away from Sesame Street. Guest: Lin-Manuel Miranda.

episodes.name: Battle of the Chefs
episodes.overview: Chris and Elmo help Alan compete in challenges to become the “Cast Iron Cook.” Guests: Jason Schwartzman, Anthony Mackie.

episodes.name: Hello Rudy
episodes.overview: Abby is excited to meet her new stepbrother, Rudy, for the first time. Rosita and Elmo help Abby look out for him so that she can see Rudy as soon as he gets to Sesame Street.

episodes.name: Rudy Lets Loose
episodes.overview: Abby and Rosita help watch Grover’s dogs, but Rudy scares the animals when he tries to pet them. Rudy uses Abby’s wand and turns himself into a dog so that the dogs will be friends with him.

episodes.name: Hide and Seek Rudy
episodes.overview: After Rudy uses Abby’s wand to find the best hiding spot, and accidentally turns himself into a banana, she becomes worried when she can’t find him.

episodes.name: The Four Sneezons
episodes.overview: When Grover wishes he didn’t have a cold in the fall, Rudy uses Abby’s wand to change the season. Now, every time Grover sneezes, the seasons keep changing.

episodes.name: Snazzy Society (repeat)
episodes.overview: When Segi becomes upset after reading a book about her favorite character, Mando, Chris and Leela help her see that being brown is snazzy. Guest star: Lupita Nyong’o.

47.name: Season 47
47.overview: Season 47 brings exciting new changes, including a reimagined 'Elmo's World,' a new kindness curriculum, and new Muppet characters.

episodes.name: A Sesame Street Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: Elmo, Big Bird, Rosita, Alan, Julia, Nina and the rest of the neighborhood gather to appreciate all the traditions, cultures and delicious foods their community has to offer.

episodes.name: Cinderella's Slippery Slippers
episodes.overview: Cinderella would rather play than open her new shoe store and be a princess; Rosita tells Cinderella she can solve both of her problems if she gets a pair of sneakers like hers from the new store.

episodes.name: Elmo's Nursery Rhyme
episodes.overview: Mother Goose tries to write a nursery rhyme for Elmo, but doesn't know anything about him; Abby tells Mother Goose some of the things that make Elmo special.

episodes.name: Rapunzel Gets a Haircut
episodes.overview: Abby and Elmo help Rapunzel figure out how to keep her hair from getting in the way so she can follow her dream of becoming a gymnast.

episodes.name: Martian Mission
episodes.overview: Martians arrive on Sesame Street to find out what Earth people are like; Elmo shows them around and helps them learn that people come in lots of sizes, their skin comes in lots of colors, and people speak lots of languages.

episodes.name: Clothing Drive
episodes.overview: Rudy's favorite sweater no longer fits him, so Nina suggests having a clothing drive where everyone can give clothes they do not need to people who do need them; Rudy's sweater goes to a little girl who is very excited to wear it.

episodes.name: M Is for Missing
episodes.overview: The letter M goes missing all over Sesame Street, and it is up to Nina and the gang to find it.

episodes.name: Abby's Sock Solution
episodes.overview: Abby tries to help Chris after he loses a sock while doing laundry, but her efforts create chaos when she conjures up dancing socks.

episodes.name: Our Family's Way
episodes.overview: Abby's family has dinner at Elmo's house and learns that even though they do things differently, everybody can have fun working together to get dinner ready.

episodes.name: Last Straw
episodes.overview: Bert searches for a quiet place to nap after Ernie makes too much noise; after spending time apart, Bert and Ernie apologize to each other and learn that even though they had a fight, they can still be friends.

episodes.name: Kitty Kindness
episodes.overview: When a lost kitten gets discovered on Sesame Street, Chris and Elmo put up signs to try and find its owner; Grover and Cookie Monster help look after the kitten and learn how to take care of it.

episodes.name: Hair Training
episodes.overview: Prairie and her friend Gabrielle are practicing a dance, but their hair doesn’t move the same way. Nina helps them realize that the dance is even more fun when they each let their hair do what it wants to do! Elmo and Big Bird join in and let their fur and feathers fly free.

episodes.name: Book Worming
episodes.overview: Elmo's friend Zuzu is visiting Sesame Street from South Africa. After reading all about her home in the Book Nook, Elmo and Alan throw Zuzu a welcome party with South African food, music and traditional clothing. At the party, Zuzu says she read up on Sesame Street, too.

episodes.name: Chinese New Year
episodes.overview: It's Chinese New Year on Sesame Street! To learn how some people celebrate the holiday in China and around the world, Nina helps Elmo, Abby Cadabby, Cookie Monster and Grover build their own dragon costume. (Guest: John Legend).

episodes.name: Chamki Visits Sesame Street
episodes.overview: Big Bird is getting ready for a visit from Chamki, his pen pal from India. Grover, Elmo, Rosita and Cookie Monster build a giant bird feeder to help her feel comfortable on Sesame Street. When she gets there, the gang finds out that even though she and Big Bird have a lot in common, she's not a bird at all!

episodes.name: Street Food
episodes.overview: Lily, a four-year-old tiger cub from China, joins Chamki, Zuzu, and all their new friends for an international food festival on Sesame Street. The group learns about traditional dishes from Japan, South Africa, India, and China. Rudy is reluctant to try the unfamiliar foods, but he’s pleasantly surprised when Elmo, Abby, and Chris encourage him to taste a few.

episodes.name: Crafty Friends
episodes.overview: Elmo helps Zoe find just the right play date for her pet rock, Rocco.

episodes.name: It's Dance Your Favorite Dance Day
episodes.overview: Nina knows a lot of dances from around the world, and she's able to teach everyone the moves to their favorite dances.

episodes.name: Me Am Cookie Monster
episodes.overview: Cookie Monster defends his identity when rumors start swirling that he's really Veggie Monster.

episodes.name: Elmo's Butterfly Friend
episodes.overview: Elmo and Telly learn how a caterpillar turns into a butterfly through metamorphosis.

episodes.name: Shape Hunt
episodes.overview: Everyone on Sesame Street is getting ready to play Shape Hunt. Each team gets a list of shapes and they have to look closely around the street to find them. When both teams have difficulty finding shapes on their list, Julia helps by finding shapes in places no one else thought of.

episodes.name: The Helpful Cloud
episodes.overview: Elmo and Grover help Floatie the Cloud try to find a job on Sesame Street; Chris helps Floatie realize that she already has an important job by bringing rain to help plants and flowers grow and giving shade to keep everyone cool on hot, sunny days.

episodes.name: The Happy To Be Me Club
episodes.overview: Big Bird feels bad about himself after being teased, but Abby reminds him that he is special.

episodes.name: My Rhaki Family
episodes.overview: Chris, Telly and Zoe visit the Laundromat and find Leela making a bracelet. She explains today is "Rahki", an Indian holiday for brothers and sisters where they exchange bracelets (also including people they feel are like brother and sister).

episodes.name: The Wheel Deal
episodes.overview: Nina cleans out the bike shop, and Oscar wants everything for his trash collection; the Three Pigs Movers figure out how to use wheels to help them move heavy items to Oscar's can.

episodes.name: Grandparent's Day
episodes.overview: Elmo is disappointed when his grandparents get stuck at the airport while on their way to visit him for the Grandparents Celebration on Sesame Street.

episodes.name: The New Old MacDonald
episodes.overview: Old MacDonald's animals don't want to sing their song anymore because it's always sung the same way, so Nina and the gang figure out how they could sing the song in a fun new way.

episodes.name: Oscar the Kind
episodes.overview: When Oscar the Grouch gets sick, he doesn’t feel grouchy anymore … he feels kind! Elmo and Baby Bear see how easy and fun it is to be kind to others.

episodes.name: Elmo and Abby's Bubble Fun
episodes.overview: Alan and Chris introduce Sesame Street's first-ever Bubble Fest! Elmo, Abby, Telly and the kids gather for the festivities. Telly is excited, as he's never blown a bubble before, and neither has Abby (her mommy's always made them with magic).

episodes.name: The Golden Triangle
episodes.overview: Texas Telly joins Minnesota Mel in a search for the Golden Triangle of Destiny.

episodes.name: Fido the Frog
episodes.overview: Chris, Elmo and Abby help Fido feel proud that he is a frog and find the right habitat to live in.

episodes.name: Abby and Zoe Love Karate
episodes.overview: Nina teaches Abby and Zoe all about karate. After learning how to focus and practice, Abby and Zoe manage to kick a ball off a stand with a special karate kick.

episodes.name: Rosita and Elmo Teach Yoga
episodes.overview: Telly practices balancing his weight during yoga class.

episodes.name: Surfin' Sesame Street
episodes.overview: Alan tells Elmo and Grover that he couldn't go on vacation this year, so Elmo, Grover and Chris surprise him by bringing the beach to Sesame Street.

episodes.name: The Count's Counting Error
episodes.overview: Upset by his first-ever counting mistake, the Count tries to find another job. He soon finds out that many other jobs include counting, too.

48.name: Season 48
48.overview: The word on the street is 'kindness' in Season 48 of this award-winning series that features a new segment: 'Cookie Monster's Foodie Truck.'

episodes.name: When You're a Vet
episodes.overview: Abby and Elmo play veterinarians. By using their eyes, ears and hands, Abby and Elmo figure out what's wrong with their pretend patients and help them feel better.

episodes.name: Picture This
episodes.overview: Alan gives Elmo, Rosita and Abby his old cameras to play with and suggests they can be photographers for the day; Abby, Rosita and Elmo go around Sesame Street learning how to use their cameras and taking pictures of things like sports and fashion.

episodes.name: Hey! Sesame Street News
episodes.overview: Chris's belt buckle is missing! Newspaper journalist Cookie Monster solves the mystery by asking the five W questions: who, what, where, when, why.

episodes.name: So You Think You Can Choreograph
episodes.overview: Elmo and his friends are making a music video; when they ask Zoe to be the choreographer, she comes up with the perfect dance and teaches everyone the moves.

episodes.name: Elmo's Factory
episodes.overview: Elmo invents something new – “Anything Holders” – but he needs help with the assembly. Chris helps Elmo and his friends put together their own factory, and they work as a team and each take on a different job to make the “Anything Holders” more quickly.

episodes.name: Math Magic (repeat)
episodes.overview: Max the Magician appears on Sesame Street, doing magic tricks that make scarves appear and cards disappear.

episodes.name: New Year's Eve on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: It’s New Year’s Eve on Sesame Street! Rosita and Telly try to help Elmo stay awake until midnight so he can celebrate with his friends.

episodes.name: Play Time
episodes.overview: The gang is putting on a play about Little Miss Muffet, the classic nursery rhyme. Nina helps Big Bird take on the role of playwright when he has an idea for a new ending.

episodes.name: Bath Time for Blanky
episodes.overview: Abby brings Rudy to the laundromat to wash his stinky blanket, but new attendant Grover doesn't know how to use the machines; luckily, Chris brings in his dirty clothes too, and shows everyone how to use a washing machine and dryer.

episodes.name: Astronaut Elmo
episodes.overview: Rosita, Elmo and Abby pretend to be astronauts and use their imaginations to go into space; with help from Chris, they figure out which "space tool" to use to fix their ripped spaceship.

episodes.name: Honk If You Love Libraries
episodes.overview: With the help of librarian Grover and comic book superhero Galactic Gail (Zoe Kravitz), Nina and Elmo tour the different sections of the local library to find the books they need.

episodes.name: Elmo's Happy Little Train
episodes.overview: Elmo, Rosita, and Zoe play train and pretend to be the driver, conductor and passenger. They make up an adventure so that Oscar can play, too.

episodes.name: The Big Pretend Band
episodes.overview: Bert learns how to use his imagination and pretend-play a saxophone so that he can join his friends in their pretend band and play in a concert.

episodes.name: Sesame Friendship
episodes.overview: Big Bird is building a tall block castle, but it accidentally gets knocked down. Big Bird thinks Snuffy did it and doesn't let him explain. Alan and Nina help them learn to stand up for themselves, listen to each other and apologize.

episodes.name: Rudy Rides the Bus
episodes.overview: Elmo and Rudy play bus driver and bus monitor, driving a homemade bus and helping their friends get around Sesame Street.

episodes.name: Mechanics in Space
episodes.overview: Rudy pretends to be a space alien; when his spaceship won't start, Abby and Elmo play mechanics and fix it.

episodes.name: Fixing X
episodes.overview: Big Bird and Snuffy are the hosts of "The Letter of the Day Show" on Sesame Street, and learn all about how the letter X can come at the end of a word.

episodes.name: Elmo Goes to Chicken School
episodes.overview: Elmo helps Professor Buck Awe teach a class of chickens using strategies he learned in preschool.

episodes.name: Walking the Dog
episodes.overview: Elmo wants to be a dog walker just like dog walker Grover; his friends help him practice by pretending to be different kinds of dogs.

episodes.name: Elmo the Engineer
episodes.overview: Elmo and his dad become engineers as they design a device to help Elmo put away his toys.

episodes.name: Julia's Haircut
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby and Alan play hair salon and pretend to be hair stylists to help Julia feel less scared about getting a haircut.

episodes.name: Dinosaur in the Laundromat
episodes.overview: There’s a strange noise on Sesame Street, and Rudy, Zoe, and Rosita suspect it’s a dinosaur! With the help of Bill Nye, they become scientists to observe, ask questions, and investigate the mystery.

episodes.name: Earth Day
episodes.overview: Rudy learns to be kind to the Earth after he sees what it would be like if everyone acted like him and threw their trash on the street.

episodes.name: Four Furry Superheroes
episodes.overview: Telly, Abby and Elmo pretend to be their favorite superheroes, The Furry Four.

episodes.name: Welcome to Sesame Hospital
episodes.overview: Rosita, Abby, and Telly play hospital and pretend to be a doctor, nurse and x-ray technician. Chris pretends to be their patient and they help heal his funny bone.

episodes.name: Wild Adventure on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: “Wild Nature Survivor Guy” tries to survive out in the wilds of Sesame Street.

episodes.name: Little Bo Peep Lost Her Cow
episodes.overview: Little Bo Peep has lost her...cow. Telly and Elmo, the Cowmonster Pair, are on the case!

episodes.name: How to Build a Dinosaur
episodes.overview: Grover, Elmo, and Rosita are imagining that they are paleontologists, a scientist who digs through dirt and stones to find fossils.

episodes.name: Oscar Uncanned
episodes.overview: Someone has taken Oscar's trash can! With Abby and Rudy's help, Oscar finds out that it was a sanitation worker who took his trash can.

episodes.name: Counting Critters
episodes.overview: Bert and Ernie are animal-sitting six animals, but the animals sneak outside onto Sesame Street. Bert and Ernie ask Alan and Elmo for their help to make sure they find all six animals.

episodes.name: Grocery Games
episodes.overview: To make food shopping more fun, Alan turns it into a game. Can Elmo, Abby, and Cookie Monster find three foods that start with the letter C in different sections of the supermarket before Alan finishes checking out?

episodes.name: Baby Bear's Just Right Cafe
episodes.overview: Baby Bear, Elmo, and Abby play restaurant. Alan teaches them how to pretend to be the chef, the host, and the server. Goldilocks is their first diner, and she’ll decide if everything is “just right.”

episodes.name: Camp Grover
episodes.overview: Elmo tells his friends that he's going to summer camp, but he's never been before. They pretend to go to Camp Grover for the day and learn all about the fun things that can happen.

episodes.name: Slimey at the Car Race
episodes.overview: Slimey participates in the Squirmadega car race.

episodes.name: Cookie Monster's Museum Mystery
episodes.overview: A brand-new museum has opened on Sesame Street - the Museum of Modern Cookie! Cookie Monster, Elmo and Chris are very excited to check it out. While walking around the museum, the paintings suddenly begin to disappear and the museum guards think Cookie Monster stole them. With Abby's help, Cookie Monster, Elmo and Chris catch who really was taking the cookie art. Season finale.

49.name: Season 49
49.overview: Season 49 brings exciting new changes to the Street and features a host of A-list celebrity appearances.

episodes.name: Big Bird Across America
episodes.overview: Big Bird wants to visit Cousin Bird in California, but he learns that it’s too far for him to walk! Nina suggests a cross-country road trip, so they can stop off to meet new friends along the way.

episodes.name: The Great Sesame Street Cake Off
episodes.overview: Cookie Monster and Gonger team up against Grover and Alan in a competition to see who can bake the best birthday cake for Nina. Elmo and Rosita help the two teams work together, combining one team’s cake and the other team’s frosting to make the ultimate birthday treat.

episodes.name: Pigs for Another Day
episodes.overview: After the three little pigs catch a cold, Grover, Rosita and Cookie Monster become "Pigs for a Day." They make a couple of mistakes, but they keep trying until they build the right-sized doghouse for Chris’ friend.

episodes.name: Getting Dressed, Not Stressed
episodes.overview: Elmo wants to play with his friends in the snow, but he gets frustrated when he tries to get dressed. With help from his friend Jacket, Elmo remembers to take a deep breath and keep trying until he gets dressed in his winter clothes.

episodes.name: A Dog and a Song!
episodes.overview: When Elmo and Abby can't find a band for their friend Mick to sing in, they come up with the idea of making their own band. The music sounds just right for him.

episodes.name: Game Day on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: Sesame Street has turned into a giant board game called Sesame Stoplight and Elmo, Abby, and Rudy are ready to play. When feeling frustrated during the game, they learn to stop and take a deep breath, think of a plan to solve the problem and then go try their plan. By working together and not giving up, they complete the challenges and win the game.

episodes.name: Grouch University
episodes.overview: Sesame Street friends become part of Oscar's experiments when he enrolls in an online class to get his degree in Grouch Science.

episodes.name: A Recipe for Dance
episodes.overview: Chris and Rudy have trouble learning the dance moves in Nina's dance class so they sneak out and leave. They realize that they shouldn't give up so they practice and work together to learn the dance pattern and go back to join dance class.

episodes.name: Humpty Dumpty's Football Dream
episodes.overview: When Humpty Dumpty decides to join the King's Horses & Men in their annual football game, Telly tries to come up with the right protective gear to keep Humpty from cracking.

episodes.name: Abby Poofs a Party
episodes.overview: Abby helps Leela get dressed for a neighborhood party, even if she doesn't need the assistance.

episodes.name: The Great Fruit Strike
episodes.overview: When the pineapples, bananas, and other fruits get tired of being passed over at snack time, they decide to leave Sesame Street. The gang gets together to sing songs about how much they appreciate fruit to get them to stay.

episodes.name: Elmo's Good Luck Charm
episodes.overview: Elmo loses his lucky baseball card before a game of tee-ball and says he can't play without it. When Abby, Alan, and Rosita tell Elmo that all he needs to do is practice, Elmo learns that he can still play without his lucky card.

episodes.name: A New Friend on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: There's a new face on Sesame Street! With Elmo and Rosita’s help, military kid Charlie finds her way around the neighborhood and learns that Sesame Street is a place where everyone can be friends - no matter how different they are.

episodes.name: Let's Draw
episodes.overview: Rudy feels upset when he “ruins” a drawing. Alan encourages him to keep trying, and Rudy eventually creates a new picture inspired by his mistake.

episodes.name: There's a New Count in Town
episodes.overview: Charlie is counting everything on Sesame Street so the Count decides to leave, thinking he’s not needed anymore. But there’s too much to count for Charlie on her own so she asks for the Count’s help. Charlie explains that she loves to count but she could never take his place. The Count agrees to stay and he and Charlie continuing counting together.

episodes.name: You Can Do It, Elmo
episodes.overview: When Abby uses magic to improve Elmo’s basketball abilities, Elmo learns there are no shortcuts when it comes to mastering a skill.

episodes.name: Magic Spell
episodes.overview: The princess is under a magic sleeping spell and the spell can only be broken if the Prince writes his name on a magic tablet. Elmo and Abby help Prince Billy practice and encourages him to keep trying until he learns how to write his name all by himself.

episodes.name: What Floats Rocco's Boat
episodes.overview: Elmo and Zoe try to figure out how to make Rocco the rock float. Leela helps them experiment with different materials until they design the perfect vessel.

episodes.name: Comic Book Adventures
episodes.overview: Elmo and Abby make their very own comic books, but Elmo makes a mistake drawing his story and doesn't want anyone to see it. With Chris' help, Elmo learns that he can use his imagination to change the story and make it anything he wants it to be.

episodes.name: Neighborhood Safari
episodes.overview: Grover takes Elmo and friends on a Sesame Street Safari and they pretend to be all of the wild animals they see.

episodes.name: The Fluffster Kerfuffle
episodes.overview: When Rudy tries to use Julia’s special toy, Fluffster, as part of a game he’s playing with Elmo and Abby Cadabby, Julia gets very upset. Alan explains that Fluffster helps Julia feel calm, so it’s not a toy she likes to share. Rudy apologizes, and the friends find a different way to play together.

episodes.name: The Disappoint-O-Meter
episodes.overview: Oscar tries to find someone who's feeling disappointed by using his new disappoint-o-meter but he accidentally helps them feel happy again.

episodes.name: Zoe Breaks Her Arm
episodes.overview: When Zoe slips and breaks her arm during a ballet jump, she finds it difficult to play or do anything fun with her arm in a cast. The gang works together to put a twist on “If You're Happy and You Know It,” so Zoe can join in.

episodes.name: Dog Day Engineers
episodes.overview: Zoe and Rosita help Nina dog sit but their arms get tired after continuously throwing the balls. They don't give up and keep thinking of a way to solve this problem. They figure out how to design a bike-powered ball-throwing machine they can pedal using their feet. They are two real engineers!

episodes.name: A Very Special Fiesta
episodes.overview: Charlie, Grover, Rudy, and Abby help Rosita and her abuela plan for a friend’s fiesta. While trying to figure out what they need for the party, they try to guess who Rosita and her abuela’s friend could be.

episodes.name: Back to Nature
episodes.overview: Abby and Rudy want to bring nature inside Hooper's so Chris can feel like he’s outside. Abby uses her mom’s magic wand but makes a mistake and fills Hooper’s with too many animals and plants. Abby apologizes for using her mom’s wand without permission and together, with her mom, she learns how to fix her mistake without using magic.

episodes.name: Welcome Baby Chicks
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, Bert, and Ernie have to be patient and wait for baby chicks to hatch. By singing and making arts and crafts together, they learn that time can fly when you’re having fun.

episodes.name: Searching For Letter Y
episodes.overview: Telly, Elmo, and Abby become knights and go on a quest to help an AM Letter "Y" find its purpose in life.

episodes.name: The Treasure of Yucky Mama
episodes.overview: During Oscar the Grouch’s spring “cleaning,” he finds a fifty-year-old treasure map - but the neighborhood looks much different than it used to! Will Elmo, Abby, Nina, Oscar, and Charlie learn enough about Sesame Street’s history to complete three grouchy challenges and find Yucky Mama's treasure?

episodes.name: Making the Band
episodes.overview: A rock star is performing on Sesame Street, but his equipment is in the wrong town so the gang helps build and design replacements so the show can go on.

episodes.name: Rudy Blows His First Bubble
episodes.overview: Rudy feels frustrated that he can't blow a bubble. With help from Elmo, Alan, and Rosita, Rudy realizes that he needs to breathe out instead of breathing in when blowing a bubble.

episodes.name: Big Bird's Fairy Tale
episodes.overview: Big Bird makes up a fairy tale about a bird named Birdie who helps a Beast learn how to be a good friend.

episodes.name: Lucky's Unlucky Day
episodes.overview: It's Lucky's first day on the job as a bulldozer; when he gets upset about making mistakes, Big Bird and Nina tell him that it's ok to make mistakes and explain that Lucky just needs to say, "I can do it," and try again.

episodes.name: Fourth of July Celebration
episodes.overview: It's July Fourth on Sesame Street! Elmo, Abby Cadabby, and Rudy look for the perfect birthday present for America, but Alan teaches them that holidays are really about spending time with family and friends. Together, they do something kind for all their neighbors.

episodes.name: Let's Go Camping
episodes.overview: Chris and Elmo are excited to be camping in the woods! All kinds of animals join Chris and Elmo for the camp out. After Chris finds the right kind of food for each animal, they all eat dinner together. Elmo and Chris both agree they should have a sleepover like this every night! Season finale.

50.name: Season 50
50.overview: Season 50 focuses on the power of possibilities, empowering kids to take safe risks and learn from their mistakes.

episodes.name: Ramp Racers
episodes.overview: Elmo and Rosita want to race their ping-pong balls, but the only ramp on Sesame Street is being used. This is a problem! They wonder if they can make another ramp. What if they use cardboard? Let’s try! It works. With Julia’s help, Elmo and Rosita didn’t give up, and they built two long ramps. They all get a chance to race their ping-pong balls – Julia, too!

episodes.name: Camp Out
episodes.overview: Abby, Rudy, Elmo, and Charlie are camping out on Sesame Street. They’re just about to toast marshmallows when the sweet treats suddenly disappear! Together, the friends look and listen for clues to find out where their marshmallows have gone.

episodes.name: Measuring Big Bird
episodes.overview: Nina is using a smiley face growth chart to measure how tall Elmo and Rosita are. Big Bird wants to see how tall he is too, but Nina is all out of smiley faces. What else can they use to measure their tall friend? After trying a few ideas, inspiration strikes. What if they make their own smiley faces? It works! Because they didn’t give up, all the friends—including Big Bird—could be measured.

episodes.name: Bye Bye Boo Boos
episodes.overview: Boo-Boo Busters Elmo and Abby go around Sesame Street in search of friends who need help making their boo-boos feel better.

episodes.name: Cardboard Castle
episodes.overview: Issa Rae is a Queen who doesn’t have enough bricks to build a play castle for her daughter. This is a problem! Elmo, Cookie Monster, and Rosita wonder: can they use something else to build the castle? What about cardboard boxes and tubes? The three friends give it a try—and it works. Because they didn’t give up, they built a cardboard castle fit for a Princess!

episodes.name: Holiday at Hooper's
episodes.overview: It’s holiday time on Sesame Street! When their parents run late from the holiday concert, Elmo and Baby Bear stay with Alan and Nina at Hooper's Store. But they are disappointed not to celebrate Christmas Eve and Hanukkah as they had planned. Elmo, Baby Bear, Nina, and Alan sing carols, eat latkes, and make lots of decorations. They create a wonderful holiday celebration all by themselves—and Elmo and Baby Bear realize that the best part of holidays is being together with friends and family.

episodes.name: It's Sesame Circus
episodes.overview: Elmo wonders what amazing and exciting act he can perform for Sesame Circus, but he's struggling to figure it out. Then he has an idea! What if he rides his tricycle down a ramp and through a hoop? Let's try!

episodes.name: Return of the Fairytale Helpers
episodes.overview: When the gingerbread house from "Hansel and Gretel" falls, the Fairytale Helpers wonder what might hold the walls together. What if they use frosting? Let's try!

episodes.name: Sneeze a Season
episodes.overview: Grover wishes he didn't have a cold in the Fall, so Rudy uses Abby's wand to change the season. Now every time Grover sneezes, the seasons keep changing.

episodes.name: Huff and Puff Away
episodes.overview: After Chris reads the story of the Three Little Pigs, Elmo wonders if they can change the story so the wolf isn't mean.

episodes.name: Tough Monster Race
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, Grover, and Nina want to make an obstacle course on Sesame Street. But they don’t have anything to go over, under, around, or through. They wonder what they can find around them to make these obstacles. What if they use a broom to go over, a blanket to go under, pool noodles to go around, and a cardboard box to go through? It works! The friends made the best monster obstacle course ever.

episodes.name: The Waiting Game
episodes.overview: Here is a long line at Hooper's and Elmo and Rosita are feeling frustrated; they don't want to wait for their turn. This is a problem!

episodes.name: Elmo and the Healthy Heroes
episodes.overview: The healthy Super Food Super Heroes help Elmo and his friends find and try new, colorful healthy snacks and learn that breakfast is the most important meal, giving them the energy they need for the day.

episodes.name: The Counting Booth Counters
episodes.overview: The Count leaves his counting booth in the hands of an excited Elmo and Abby, who learn how to count in different ways.

episodes.name: The Cool Tool Kid
episodes.overview: When Elmo's, Rosita's, and Bert's toys get stuck in different places, Charlie and Super Grover wonder what tool might help them reach all their friends' things. What if they use a baton? Let's try!

episodes.name: The Glitter Jar
episodes.overview: Nina is feeling frustrated as she tries to fix her scooter. Elmo and Grover wonder how they can help Nina calm down. What if they make her glitter jars? Let's try!

episodes.name: Abby, Zoe, and Rosita Make a Story
episodes.overview: Rosita helps Abby and Zoe think outside the box to imagine the best fairytale ever!

episodes.name: The Rainy Day Play
episodes.overview: Zoe and Rosita want to draw with chalk outside but it's raining! They become scientists and try a couple ideas, and wonder if there's something they can use that would keep them dry in the rain. What if they use art smocks that keep them dry when they paint? Zoe and Rosita didn't give up and they used the art smocks to keep the sidewalk dry. Now Zoe and Rosita can draw outside with chalk!

episodes.name: The Bike Shop Music Band
episodes.overview: To help attract new customers to the bike shop, Nina and her friends make musical instruments out of bike parts.

episodes.name: Potluck Pickle
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, Cookie Monster and Gover want to bring vegetable lasagna to Sesame Street's potluck party, but they don't have the right ingredients and their oven is broken.

episodes.name: We Wonder What Happened to Snowman
Elmo and Rosita's Tallest Block Tower Ever
Abby Airlines
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, Rudy and Chris run out of cardboard while making a pretend airplane.

episodes.name: Move and Groove on Sesame Street

51.name: Season 51
51.overview: Season 51 focuses on demonstrating playful problem solving.

episodes.name: Elmo Builds a Robot Dog
episodes.overview: Elmo, Tamir, and Alan build a robot dog for Norbert the Robot, but the tail isn’t upright and “waggedy” like Tango’s tail. What if they use a wooden paint brush and wrap it with shiny foil? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Elmo Mails a Letter
episodes.overview: Elmo is mailing his first letter and follows mail carrier Ms. Hampton to the post office, where he sees how everyone’s mail gets sorted to go to the right place. Celebrity guest Jon Batiste sings about the heroes in our neighborhoods.

episodes.name: Lunchtime Engineers
episodes.overview: When Chris sprains his ankle, Zoe, Gabrielle, and Rosita use a rope and pulley to bring him his lunch, but the rope slips off the lunch bag. What if they put the lunch bag in a basket and tie the rope to the basket handle? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Sesame Street Art Museum
episodes.overview: Everyone is making a painting to hang in Sesame Street’s art museum. Rudy wants to paint a rainbow, but he can’t make the perfect purple. What if he mixes the red and blue paint a little bit at a time? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Bug Scouts
episodes.overview: Bug Scouts Elmo, Abby, and Cookie Monster want to help Artie the Ant carry a heavy crumb. They try pushing the crumb, but it’s too heavy to move. What if they break the crumb into smaller pieces? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Doggie Job Search
episodes.overview: Brandeis, a yellow Labrador Retriever, is looking for a job on Sesame Street, so Gina trains him for a career as a service dog!

episodes.name: The Grouch Band
episodes.overview: Oscar is getting ready for a virtual Grouch concert with the noisiest and most annoying instruments. Elmo’s Shaky Shake instrument isn’t noisy enough for the concert. What if he adds more rocks and blocks to his jar? Let’s try!

episodes.name: The Letter M Mystery
episodes.overview: The letter “M” goes missing from everywhere around Sesame Street, and it’s up to Nina and the gang to find it.

episodes.name: Hike Pirates
episodes.overview: Abby, Rudy, and Freddy are going on a hike. Rudy says he’s tired and wants to go home. To make their hike more fun, Freddy shows Abby and Rudy a map they can follow to find the hidden treasure left by hike pirates.

episodes.name: Martin Luther King Jr. Day
episodes.overview: Elmo and his friends are making a Peace Tree to celebrate Martin Luther King Jr. Day. They each draw a picture to show how they will carry on Dr. King’s wish by treating people fairly and kindly every day!

episodes.name: Let's Play Pretend
episodes.overview: When Prairie Dawn organizes costumes for the Dress Me Up Club, she learns that anyone can dress-up and play any way they want.

episodes.name: Astro Team Alpha
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, and Cookie Monster are playing a space game, driving rovers back to the rocket ship before it blasts off, but then Cookie gets stuck in a crater. What if they push a pile of dirt to make a ramp? Let’s try!

episodes.name: A Trip to the Dentist
episodes.overview: To help remind Julia what happens when you visit the dentist, Elmo, Charlie, and Alan play “pretend dentist” with her. After they count and clean a toy alligator’s teeth, they learn that dentists help keep our teeth clean and healthy.

episodes.name: The Hair Dance
episodes.overview: Gabrielle and Prairie Dawn think they can’t dance together because their hair doesn’t move the same way, but Nina helps them realize that it would be cool to let their hair do whatever it wants to do.

episodes.name: Let's Grow Together
episodes.overview: Welcome to the Sesame Street community garden! Tamir has an idea: open a garden stand to share what they grow. Alan shares his grandmother’s pickled daikon recipe. Alan's proud of his heritage and happy to be sharing his family’s culture

episodes.name: The Super Shape Heroes
episodes.overview: Telly, Elmo, and Rosita transform themselves into shapes to help people.

episodes.name: Fort Rudy
episodes.overview: Elmo and Rudy are having a sleepover and building a pillow fort  but they don't have a pillow big enough for the roof. This is a problem! They wonder what they can use to build a strong and sturdy roof. What if they use a blanket and weigh it down with heavy books so it doesn't fall down? Let's try! It works. Elmo and Rudy didn't give up and built a pillow fort. Let the sleepover begin!

episodes.name: Kind Alan
episodes.overview: Elmo  Rosita  and Julia are disappointed that their plans changed  and they can't have storytime with Alan right now. To help the waiting  they paint pictures of all the kind things Alan has done for them  like giving them snacks  playing with them  and reading them books. They come up with the idea of putting the paintings together to make their own book and then tell their new story to Alan.

episodes.name: Sesame Street Goes to the Farm
episodes.overview: Elmo, Bert, Rosita and Ernie visit a farm, where they learn a lot about the machines, animals and food that can be found there.

52.name: Season 52
52.overview: Join Elmo and the gang as they welcome Tango to the neighborhood, and explore more playful problem-solving with the phrase, “I Wonder…What if…Let’s Try!”

episodes.name: Community Mural
episodes.overview: Friends on Sesame Street are painting a mural to celebrate the people in their neighborhood. When Abby has a hard time finding a paint color that is the same as her fur, she learns to mix paint to make a color that looks just like her.

episodes.name: Sesame Street Super Heroes
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, and Rosita are playing superheroes! When Elmo and Abby suggest Rosita play Super Carga, who can turn on superpowers with a Spanish catchphrase, she shares that speaking Spanish isn’t the only thing that makes her special.

episodes.name: Kind Rudy
episodes.overview: Elmo and Rudy are helping Abby out in the garden because she hurt her wrist, and Rudy wonders how else he can help, too. What if he holds the door for Chris, who is holding the bag of soil, waters the flowers, cleans up paint left out at the community center, and makes a get-well card for Abby's wrist? Just because some things are done doesn't mean you can't help. There are so many ways to be kind!

episodes.name: The Great Corn Festival
episodes.overview: Welcome to the Sesame Street Corn Party, where every family brings special food made from corn. Rosita brings pineapple tamales from a special recipe she makes with her Abuela. Together, everyone learns about the many ways corn is used and that by sharing special foods, they share something special about themselves.

episodes.name: Jobs Day
episodes.overview: It’s Jobs Day! Elmo and his friends are learning about jobs they would like to do when they grow up. When Gabrielle doesn’t know what she wants to do yet, she learns that if you work hard and practice, you can do anything you want to do. First lady and teacher Jill Biden teaches Elmo, Abby, and Tamir about all different types of jobs.

episodes.name: Bert's Bike Day with Luis
episodes.overview:
Luis and Ernie help Bert gain the confidence to ride his bike without training wheels after they break.

In loving memory of Emilio Delgado, our beloved Luis.

episodes.name: Happy Hair Day
episodes.overview: Elmo and his friends are singing about hair! They all sing together about how hair is part of what makes each of them special no matter how it grows.

episodes.name: Rudy's Favorite Sweater
episodes.overview: When Rudy’s favorite sweater no longer fits, Nina suggests they have a clothing drive so everyone in the neighborhood can donate clothes they don’t need to those who do.

episodes.name: How to Catch a Robot Dog
episodes.overview: Elmo and Tamir need to catch Norbert’s robot dog, Alfred, but he keeps running away. What if they make a fishing pole with a magnet since Alfred is made of metal? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Big Bird's Happy To Be Me Club
episodes.overview: Big Bird wants to join the Good Bird’s Club, but the members try to bully him into changing.

episodes.name: Gold Medal Tango
episodes.overview: Elmo, Rosita, and Chris are making a doggy obstacle course for Tango. They find a hula hoop that Tango could jump through, but it won’t stand up. What if they put the hoop through the slats of two chairs? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Bubble Trouble
episodes.overview: It's national bubble week! Elmo, Rosita, Zoe, and Charlie are filling all of Sesame Street with bubbles to celebrate, but they are getting tired. They wonder if there's something that could make bubbles for them. What if they put bubble wands on an egg rack in front of a fan and spin it through a tub of soapy water? Let's try! It works. They didn't give up and Sesame Street gets filled with bubbles thanks to their new machine!

episodes.name: Nani Bird Visits
episodes.overview: Big Bird’s aunt, Nani Bird, is visiting Sesame Street from Hawaii. Nani Bird shares with Elmo, Abby Cadabby and Nina how to say “aloha,” make paper flower lei, and how to hula – all special things Big Bird’s family does in Hawaii.

episodes.name: Family Album
episodes.overview: Gabrielle and Tamir are making a family photo album for Grandma Nell. They learn about melanin and that sometimes people in a family can look alike, and sometimes they can look different, but are still the same family.

episodes.name: Rockin' with Elmo and Abby
episodes.overview: Elmo and Abby compromise to create the “Best Friend Song” from each of their favorite songs.

episodes.name: Read-and-Share
episodes.overview: Elmo, Gabrielle, and Ji-Young are at an Outdoor Library. When Ji-Young can’t find a book with all the things that make her special, she writes her own comic book with the help of her friends.

episodes.name: Just Right
episodes.overview: When James says Mia can’t play Goldilocks because she doesn’t look like her, Mia stands up for herself and James learns that the best part of acting out a story is that you can be anyone you want to be.

episodes.name: Art Rocks!
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby, and Big Bird are painting pictures in the community garden, but they don’t have any paper. What if they paint on rocks that are strong and smooth? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Cinderella's New Shoes
episodes.overview: Cinderella doesn’t want to be a princess or open her new shoe store, she only wants to play. But when she meets Rosita, who suggests she get a new pair of sneakers, Cinderella realizes she can be a princess and play.

episodes.name: Count On
episodes.overview: Grover has a new job as a kitty sitter but struggles to count the number of kitties altogether. After the Count shares a shortcut – counting on, instead of from the beginning – Grover learns to count on from where he left off.

episodes.name: Grouch-ercise
episodes.overview: Oscar's been feeling terrible all day, so Elmo, Abby, Grundgetta, and Nina try to find different exercises to help him feel better. As they set off to tell Oscar all the exercises they came up with, they find him returning from a long, grouchy walk picking up trash. Oscar feels much better and is back to feeling good and rotten.

episodes.name: Monster Truckin'
episodes.overview: Elmo and Chris are making their own monster truck jump, but they don’t have a ramp. What if they make one out of a pizza box lid? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Horsing Around
episodes.overview: Julia and Samuel are helping Elmo learn to ride a pony at a horse farm. Before riding the pony, Elmo learns how to greet, feed, and brush the pony. When it’s time to ride, Elmo feels nervous. What if he practices belly breathing? Let’s try!

episodes.name: Move and Groove on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: On Dance Your Favorite Dance Day, Nina teaches everyone the moves to their favorite dances.

episodes.name: Fans of the Fan Dance
episodes.overview: Ji-Young invites her friends Elmo, Zoe, Gabrielle, Charlie, and Tamir to join her Korean fan dance class. Together they learn how to use the fans and thank Ji-Young for sharing the dance that’s special to her and her family.

episodes.name: Make Music with Bob
episodes.overview: Bob helps Abby learn all about musical instruments and how vibration makes sound, while choosing the right instrument to play.

episodes.name: Recycling Fairy to the Rescue
episodes.overview: Redusa the Recycling Fairy helps everyone on Sesame Street recycle their old trash to help keep the earth clean and beautiful.

episodes.name: The Letter C Vacation
episodes.overview: When the letter "C" goes on vacation, all of the things that start with it also go missing – cans become fans, a cake becomes a rake, cups turn into pups. When a rested letter C returns, everyone realizes that all 26 letters are important.

episodes.name: Wash Day
episodes.overview: It’s Wash Day today, and Gabrielle gets to spend time with her Auntie, Kayla. Auntie Kayla combs, shampoos, conditions, and detangles Gabrielle’s hair. During bath time, Gabrielle’s hair is twisted up in a shower cap and at the end, Gabrielle gets to pick out a new style for her hair. Wash Day is really special to Gabrielle and her family.

episodes.name: Community Garden Cleanup
episodes.overview: Elmo and friends help clean up after their garden is blown down.

episodes.name: Love Makes a Family
episodes.overview: Relatives from all over come to celebrate Family Day.

episodes.name: Gabrielle's Amazing Maze
episodes.overview: Elmo, Abby and Cookie Monster help Gabrielle build a maze for her class pet hamster.

episodes.name: Grandparents' Day
episodes.overview: It’s Grandparents’ Day on Sesame Street! While Elmo, Tamir, and Gabrielle help Grandma Nell prepare Grandpa ZZ’s Triple Cheesy Macareenie, they learn that the best part about making it is being able to cook together as a family.

episodes.name: Ramp and Roll
episodes.overview: Elmo and Rosita wonder if they can make a ramp out of cardboard to race their ping-pong balls.

episodes.name: Sesame Street Submarine
episodes.overview: Elmo, Rosita and Rudy are making a submarine.

53.name: Season 53
53.overview: Sharpen your crayons and hide your cookies, because Season 53 of Sesame Street is coming to HBO Max, starting November 3rd! Join your favorite furry friends for more fun, laughs, and lessons devoted to helping children grow up with a healthy self-identity and sense of belonging.

episodes.name: Can They Be Friends?
episodes.overview: Reporter Grover learns that people can be friends even if they are different ages, cheer for different sports teams and like doing different things.

episodes.name: The Oct-Dough-Pus
episodes.overview: Grover and his friend, the octopus, are helping at Hooper's Store but the octopus can only cook bread. With help from his friends, Grover fulfills his customer's order while learning that families all over the world make bread in different ways, shapes, and sizes!

episodes.name: Proud of My Name
episodes.overview: Elmo, Gabrielle and Rosita join a basketball team; Elmo and Gabrielle encourage Rosita to tell the coach to call her by her actual name; Rosita is proud of her name because names are a big part of one's identity.

episodes.name: Abby's Magical Sleepover
episodes.overview: Gabrielle, Charlie and Abby are having a sleepover! As they start their bedtime routines, they learn that their routines are different and alike.

episodes.name: Sesame Street Self-Portraits
episodes.overview: Elmo, Tamir, Charlie, Julia and Cookie Monster are making self-portraits, drawing what they look like and what they love to do.

episodes.name: Scootin' on Sesame Street
episodes.overview: Elmo shares his scooter with Zoe and learns how to be patient and wait for his turn, while she practices and learns how to ride.

episodes.name: Worms Want To Play
episodes.overview: Frankie the worm wants to play with her cousins, but they moved far away. To help their friend, Rosita, Gabrielle and Zoe must think like engineers.

episodes.name: Elmo's Morning Routine
episodes.overview: Elmo and Abby help Crystal the Ball come up with a morning routine so she can be ready to go out and play.

episodes.name: Are You Ready For School?
episodes.overview: When Rudy and Zoe feel nervous about getting ready for kindergarten, Ji-Young and Baby Bear host a game show all about school to help.

episodes.name: Supermarket Games
episodes.overview: Alan creates a game to make food shopping more fun! Can Elmo, Abby and Cookie Monster get the food in Alan's cart before checking out?

episodes.name: Sesame Street Song Day
episodes.overview: Mia learns how to sing a song in Spanish with help from her friends, who tell her how special she is no matter how much or little Spanish she speaks.

episodes.name: The Flamingo Scoop
episodes.overview: When Fred the Flamingo is visiting Sesame Street for a family reunion, Elmo, Rudy and Nina learn all about flamingos.

episodes.name: A Home for Fido
episodes.overview: Chris, Elmo and Abby help Fido feel proud that he's a frog and find him the right habitat to live in.

episodes.name: Sesame Street's Lunar New Year Celebration
episodes.overview: Lily, Qui and Ji-Young are celebrating Lunar New Year on Sesame Street. They share with their friends how their families celebrate the holiday.

episodes.name: Elmo Helps the Amazing Zero!
episodes.overview: The Amazing Zero and Elmo are on Sesame Street to help take everything away when people need to get to zero.

episodes.name: The Grover Game
episodes.overview: At Street Carnival Day, Cookie Monster is playing the Grover Game and needs to move ping pong balls off a plate without touching them.

episodes.name: The Kitty Sisters
episodes.overview: Chris and Elmo put up signs to try to find a lost kitten's owner, and Grover and Cookie Monster learn all about how to take care of a kitten.

episodes.name: Tamir's Water Works
episodes.overview: Tamir needs to figure out how to keep the community garden watered while he's away at camp. With his friends' help, Tamir makes an irrigation system.

episodes.name: Bert and Ernie's Opposite Day
episodes.overview: On Opposite Day, everyone is doing things that are as different as they can be. Bert and Ernie realize they like so many opposite things too!

episodes.name: Our Family Musical
episodes.overview: For a school project, Mia writes a musical about how special it is to grow up in a family with two different cultures.

episodes.name: Elmo and Abby's Ocean Adventure
episodes.overview: After Abby turns Sesame Street into a magical ocean, Dorothy disappears, and Elmo and Abby must follow clues to find her.

episodes.name: The Feelings Fair
episodes.overview: At the Feelings Fair, Elmo, Alan and Julia learn to figure out how someone is feeling by looking at their facial expressions.

episodes.name: The Sign Language ABCs
episodes.overview: At Alphabet Day, Elmo sings the ABC song and his friend Mathis signs the alphabet using American Sign Language.

episodes.name: Jumpin' in the Rain
episodes.overview: Elmo tries to find something to do in the rain while he waits to jump in puddles.

episodes.name: Shabbat Shalom!
episodes.overview: Charlie and her family share Shabbat dinner with their friends Elmo, Alan, Big Bird and Tamir, who help them prepare their meal before sundown.

episodes.name: Elmo's Little Star
episodes.overview: Elmo keeps practicing and doesn't give up until he learns how to play "Twinkle Twinkle Little Star" on his piano.

episodes.name: The Tasty Transport
episodes.overview: Alan has a lot of food deliveries to make at Hooper's. Elmo, Charlie and Rosita ride their scooter and bikes to help deliver food to customers.

episodes.name: Tamir Learns Tagalog
episodes.overview: With help from his friend, Tamir, TJ makes a comic book gift to welcome his favorite comic book artist, Bobby Manalo, to Sesame Street.

episodes.name: Brave Bessie by Brave Gabrielle
episodes.overview: Gabrielle puts on a show to tell her friends about Bessie Coleman, the first African American and Native American woman to fly an airplane.

episodes.name: Elmo Visits the Library
